Governor Abubakar Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi State has appointed the defeated chairman of the All Progressive Congress (APC) in the just concluded state congress of the party in Kebbi State, Alhaji Attahiru Maccido, as commissioner. The Speaker of the State House of Assembly, Alhaji Sama’ila  Abdulmumeen Kamba made this known while briefing journalists at the Government House in Birnin Kebbi on Tuesday shortly after meeting with Governor Bagudu. He said the appointment of the former APC chairman and the former Secretary to the state government, Alhaji Nuradeen Kangiwa was part of the efforts taken by the APC to reconcile aggrieved members over the congresses and their nominations have been given speedy approval by the state assembly.